  "informal_statement": "Every natural number n >= 2 has a prime factor: there exists a prime p dividing n.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Strong induction on n via Nat.strong_induction_on. If n is prime, take p = n (dvd_refl). Otherwise n has a nontrivial divisor m with 2 <= m < n (Nat.exists_dvd_of_not_prime2); the strong induction hypothesis applied to m (which is strictly smaller and still >= 2) gives a prime p dividing m, and p ∣ m ∣ n gives p ∣ n by transitivity.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem exists_prime_factor (n : ℕ) (hn : 2 ≤ n) : ∃ p, Nat.Prime p ∧ p ∣ n",
