  "notes": "Proof authority: Lean kernel via the tracked proof-search loop (episode ac1ea7d4), kernel_verified on the first attempt. The packet's Lean file states n and hn as explicit theorem parameters (not a bare `intro n; intro hn` inside the tactic block, since the proof-search environment's root obligation is always a headerless `∀`-statement); this exact tactic-state form (`intro n hn` before `induction n using Nat.strong_induction_on`, confirming the induction tactic auto-reverts/reintroduces the dependent hypothesis hn) was independently kernel-verified in this episode before being packaged, per docs/proofsearch-integration.md (a prior episode f9e06b9b verified the `intro n; induction n; (case) intro hn` ordering instead, which is not the form used in the packaged file, hence the re-check). This domain's first genuine strong-induction packet (`Nat.strong_induction_on`) — every prior induction packet used plain `induction n with zero | succ`. Related to (but not proof-term-dependent on) the number_theory domain's queued `prime_two` / `not_prime_one` packets and Mathlib's own `Nat.exists_prime_and_dvd`, which this proof deliberately does not cite directly so the strong-induction technique is the one actually exercised.",
